  "text": "Cell dry weight determination. The cell dry weights of suitably diluted suspensions were determined turbidimetrically at 660 nm (microsample spectrophotometer; model 300-N; Gilford Instrument Laboratories, Inc., Oberlin, Ohio). An E6w of 1.0 was equivalent to 0.385 and 0.549 mg (dry weight) of cells per ml ofA. haloplanktis and V. fischeri, respectively. To obtain these values, fractions of cell suspensions were centrifuged to obtain packed cell preparations that were then lyophilized and dried to constant weight. The [\"4Clinulin space in packed cell preparations was also determined and used to correct for the weight of salts in the extracellular fluid in the packed cells by previously described procedures [CITATION_1] .",
